                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Parapharse.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>(Received via Taku Sept. 10, 1900.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger reports Prince Ching made a personal friendly call upon him. He says
                    edict has appointed him and Earl Li with full powers (to) settle matters. The
                    latter is expected in a few days. The Russian minister (Mr. de Giers) leaves
                    Pekin to-morrow. * * * Asks if negotiations can not be better conducted at
                    Shanghai, or at some point where telegraph communication is more rapid and
                    certain than here? Chinese commissioners should go where most convenient to
                    foreign powers.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
